ZH: 我们恰恰遇到了一起工作的机会。
EN: We just happened to come across an opportunity to work together.

ZH: 他们恰恰相反，一个喜欢夏天，一个喜欢冬天。
EN: They are precisely opposite, one likes summer while the other likes winter.

ZH: 她恰恰说到我最在意的事情。
EN: She happened to mention the thing I care about the most.

ZH: 我们恰恰赶上了最后一班火车。
EN: We happened to catch the last train.

ZH: 正在下雨的时候，我恰恰忘记带伞了。
EN: I happened to forget my umbrella right when it started raining.

ZH: 他在恰恰需要帮助的时候，我去找到了他。
EN: I went to find him just when he needed help.

ZH: 树林里的动物恰恰有着很好的自然保护。
EN: The animals in the forest have just the right natural protection.

ZH: 这匹赛马恰恰是我的最爱，它赢了比赛。
EN: This racehorse happens to be my favorite, and it won the race.

ZH: 她恰恰是我的新邻居，我们刚好搬到了隔壁。
EN: She happens to be my new neighbor, we just moved in next door.

ZH: 我恰恰前天去过这家餐厅，食物很美味。
EN: I actually went to this restaurant just the day before yesterday, the food was delicious.

ZH: 我们恰恰在街上碰到了对方。
EN: We happened to bump into each other on the street.

ZH: 这个字恰恰是我最不会写的。
EN: This character happens to be the one I struggle with the most in writing.

ZH: 她恰恰是我想到的第一个人。
EN: She is precisely the first person I thought of.

ZH: 我们恰恰去了人最多的时候，等了很久才进去。
EN: We happened to go at the busiest time, so we had to wait for a long time to get in.

ZH: 这个问题恰恰是我正在研究的。
EN: This question happens to be the one I am researching.

ZH: 他们恰恰赢了比赛的最后一场。
EN: They happened to win the last game of the competition.

ZH: 我恰恰想跟你讨论这个问题。
EN: I just happened to want to discuss this issue with you.

ZH: 特别的是他们恰恰是双胞胎兄弟。
EN: What's special is that they actually happen to be twin brothers.

ZH: 出乎意料的是他们恰恰错过了飞机。
EN: Surprisingly, they happened to miss the plane.

ZH: 他们恰恰走进教室的最后一刻。
EN: They walked into the classroom just at the very last moment.

ZH: 我们恰恰忘记给她带生日礼物了。
EN: We happened to forget to bring her a birthday gift.
